When a high school senior from Flourton, Philadelphia asked Shaun White to prom she never thought her wish would come true. Not only did the Olympic snowboarder attend her prom, he played a live show at the event with his band Bad Things.

Carly Monzo, a student at an all-girls Catholic school called Mount St. Joseph Academy learned that Shaun White had never attended his own prom before and therefore decided to make an epic video to ask him to hers.

Using a camera by GoPro, one of White's Sponsors, she filmed herself reading a witty poem and then posted the clip on Vimeo.

