The poem read, 'Roses are red, violets are blue, My name is Carly Monzo, but I'm sure you had no clue. I'm currently a senior @ an all girls school. So when it comes to dates there's no boy pool.'

'I have a six-foot rule & I know you're 5'9" but I can overlook that 'cuz DAMN you're FINE.'

After seeing the video, White decided he'd be Monzo's date but he kept his prom appearance a secret with some help from the school who fully supported his attendance.

'I didn't know that Shaun would be there until they dropped the curtain on the stage,' Monzo told The Philadelphia Daily News about her surprise.

'The dean of students called my name and I thought, 'Oh my God, what did I do?' I mean, I've spent time in her office, but it's usually for uniforms things.'

